                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-945" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CRANE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Tollington-park, Hornsey. On the 16th of May I was in Gracechurch-street, and left my gig to step into a shop—when I came out I found the prisoner in custody with my cape—this is it (<hi rend="italic">looking at it.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-946" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-946" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-946" type="surname" value="LAWRIE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-946" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES LAWRIE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a jeweller, and live in Gracechurch-street. On the 16th of May I saw Mr. Crane's gig in Gracechurch-street about four o'clock—I was at my second-floor window—he drove up right opposite my house, and went into a shop—presently the prisoner came round behind the gig, looked into it, seized the cape by the corner, pulled it gently down, and ran off with it—I opened the window, and called out "Stop him"—he threw it down, and the policeman immediately seized him.</p>
